<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">OMNH-P 43993, 21.7 mm SL, Hamahiga Island, off Okinawa Island, Ryukyu Islands, Japan, 250 m depth, 19 Sept. 2018, basket trap, K. Abe.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.J.Miller &amp; Wongrat" authorityYear="1979" class="Pisces" family="Gobiidae" genus="Egglestonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Egglestonichthys" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Egglestonichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov., OMNH-P 43993, 21.7 mm SL, Okinawa Island, Ryukyu Islands, Japan A fresh Fresh coloration B preserved Fresh coloration C radiograph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489531" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">1</figureCitation>
) with the following combination of characters: anal-fin rays I, 9; pectoral-fin rays 17, lower rays connected by membrane; longitudinal series scales 25; transverse scales 8; pre-dorsal-fin scale rows 8; cheek and opercle naked (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sketches of head region of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov. based on OMNH-P 43993, holotype, 21.7 mm SL. Note that sensory papillae have been abraded during capture A dorsal view B lateral view C ventral view. AN and PN indicate anterior and posterior nostrils, respectively. Arrowheads indicate anteroventral end of gill opening. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489532" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">2B</figureCitation>
); pelvic frenum absent; caudal fin lanceolate, its length 32.2% of SL; interorbital width very narrow, 1.2% of HL (much narrower than pupil diameter) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sketches of head region of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov. based on OMNH-P 43993, holotype, 21.7 mm SL. Note that sensory papillae have been abraded during capture A dorsal view B lateral view C ventral view. AN and PN indicate anterior and posterior nostrils, respectively. Arrowheads indicate anteroventral end of gill opening. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489532" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">2A</figureCitation>
); no spicules or odontoid processes on outer surface of gill arches; and body whitish, upper half with broken zigzag pattern of bright yellow patches and associated scattered black melanophores in fresh specimens (melanophores retained in preserved specimens) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov., OMNH-P 43993, 21.7 mm SL, Okinawa Island, Ryukyu Islands, Japan A fresh Fresh coloration B preserved Fresh coloration C radiograph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489531" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">1A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
